","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_column_hed_support-challenge","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Challenge "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"If you had a garden, what would you put in it?"}]}]}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"child-development-section","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"section-block","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_child_development_hed-green","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Child Development: Sentence Structure "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_child_development_body","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Children develop proper sentence structure mainly through repetition. As you read, have children repeat possessive sentences and pronouns after you: "},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text_emphasis","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"This is"}]},{"type":"text","text":" Lola’s "},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text_emphasis","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"garden. "}]},{"type":"text","text":"She"},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text_emphasis","elements":[{"type":"text","text":" planted it."}]},{"type":"text","text":" Encourage children to answer questions in complete sentences, pausing to model correct subject-verb agreement and plurals when necessary. "}]}]}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"day_2","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"week","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"section-block","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_top-left_header","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_top-left_header_all-caps","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"OUR EARTH"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_header_separator","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"|"}]},{"type":"text","text":"  WEEK 3: Caring for Plants"}]}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"circle-time-section","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"section-block","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_column_heds_no_paragraph_rule_day_2","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Share the Mind Builder:  Try to Help Others "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"We all have times when we need a little help. Trying to help others is a great way to show that you care! When you notice someone is sad, you can help by offering to play with them. When you see someone has lost something, you can help them find it. You can even draw or make something for someone you love to help them smile! How have you helped someone today? "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_child_development_icon"}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"section-block","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_column_heds_no_paragraph_rule_day_2","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Focus on Vocabulary "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Introduce new vocabulary.  "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_hilight_teacher_inst_new","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Use 7.3.2 Vocabulary Card. "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_vocab_words","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"plan"}]}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"story-time-section","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"section-block","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"section","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_column_heds_no_paragraph_rule","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Connect to the Book "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_hilight_teacher_inst_new","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Show the book cover. "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Today we will reread "},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_emphasis_non-ital","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Lola Plants a Garden"}]},{"type":"text","text":" by Anna McQuinn and illustrated by Rosalind Beardshaw. We will look for ways the characters help each other. "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_hilight_teacher_inst_new","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Use the Clifford Puppet. "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Clifford loves to help others! He likes to read books in which the characters help each other. That way, he can learn new ways to help his friends. "}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"section","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_column_heds_with_rule","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Close-Read: Connect to the Mind Builder "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text_routine_bold","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Focus on Patterns:"}]},{"type":"text","text":" Pause to point out patterns in the book. Challenge children to continue each pattern.  "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_d-hed_page_number","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"page 2 "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"What is Lola’s mom helping Lola do in this picture? Who helps you read your favorite books? "},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text_routine_bold","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"(MB)"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_child_development_icon"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_d-hed_page_number","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"page 5 "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"I see a pattern on Lola’s dress! The flowers are in this order: red, yellow, red, yellow. Which color comes next?  "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Lola and her mom are making a "},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_emphasis_non-ital","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"plan"}]},{"type":"text","text":". What do you think they are planning to do? "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_hilight_teacher_inst_new","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Revisit "},{"type":"element","name":"rac_highlight_teacher_inst_Italic","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"plan"}]},{"type":"text","text":" Vocabulary Card. "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_d-hed_page_number","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"page 9 "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Lola has to wait for her flowers to grow. Waiting can be hard! What would you do to help Lola have fun while she waits? "},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text_routine_bold","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"(MB)"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_child_development_icon"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_d-hed_page_number","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"pages 16–17 "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"I see a pattern in Lola’s flowers! They are planted in this order: pink, pink, orange, pink, pink, orange. The last flower is orange. Which color comes next? "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_d-hed_page_number","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"pages 18–19 "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"What is Lola’s dad helping her do in this picture? What else do you think Lola could use help with in her garden? "},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text_routine_bold","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"(MB)"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_child_development_icon"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_d-hed_page_number","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Point to page 19.  "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"How many bells are on this page? Let’s count. Now, let’s count the pink flowers. Are there the same number of bells as flowers? "}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"section","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_column_heds_with_rule","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Extended Play "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Have children help you do some research! Tell children that later this week, they will start to grow their own plants. Before that, you need to find out the best ways to care for a plant. Ask children to help you do online research to learn how to grow and care for a lima bean plant. Guide children to safely use the digital tools you have available. If you are not able to use the Internet, refer to informational texts. "}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"section","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_column_heds_with_rule","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Shared Writing "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Transcribe children’s speech as they discuss and count the steps to grow a lima bean plant."}]}]}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"child-development-section","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"section-block","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_child_development_hed-green","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Child Development: Mind Builder "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_child_development_body","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Empathy is an important step in children’s ability to help others. Children need to be able to identify that others need help and know what kind of help others need. As you read, help children find hints as to when characters may be sad or struggling to do something alone. Model thinking aloud about what you could do to help. (Denham, 2003)"}]}]}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"day_3","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"week","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"section-block","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_top-left_header","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_top-left_header_all-caps","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"OUR EARTH"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_header_separator","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"|"}]},{"type":"text","text":"  WEEK 3: Caring for Plants"}]}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"circle-time-section","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"section-block","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_column_heds_no_paragraph_rule_day_3","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Share Math Strategy  "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Hold up two Connecting Cube towers, one with six cubes and one with two. Think aloud as you compare their heights. Remind children that size can be relative."}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"section-block","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_column_heds_no_paragraph_rule_day_3","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Size Hunt "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Lead children on a “size hunt.” Guide children to look around the room for the tallest item they can find. Then have them look for the shortest item. "},{"type":"element","name":"rac_child_development_icon"}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"section-block","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_column_heds_no_paragraph_rule_day_3","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Focus on Vocabulary "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Introduce new words.  "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_hilight_teacher_inst_new","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Use 7.3.3 Vocabulary Cards. "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_vocab_words","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"tall short"}]}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"story-time-section","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"section-block","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"section","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_column_heds_no_paragraph_rule","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Revisit the Book  "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_hilight_teacher_inst_new","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Show the book cover. "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Today we are going to reread the book "},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_emphasis_non-ital","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Lola Plants a Garden"}]},{"type":"text","text":" by Anna McQuinn and illustrated by Rosalind Beardshaw. "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_hilight_teacher_inst_new","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Use the Lala Stick Puppet. "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk