acher_inst_new","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Show the Big Chart 7.3.4. "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"This week we are going to read "},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_emphasis_non-ital","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Jack and the Beanstalk."}]},{"type":"text","text":" It is a fairy tale about a boy who grows a magical plant. "}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"section","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_column_heds_with_rule","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Connect the Texts "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_emphasis_non-ital","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Lola Plants a Garden"}]},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_emphasis_non-ital","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Jack and the Beanstalk"}]},{"type":"text","text":" both focus on growing plants. Let’s look for connections between the two as we read. "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_hilight_teacher_inst_new","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Show "},{"type":"element","name":"rac_highlight_teacher_inst_Italic","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Lola Plants a Garden"}]},{"type":"text","text":" book cover. "}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"section","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_column_heds_with_rule","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Revisit the Concept Question "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"How can we help plants grow? "}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"section","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_column_heds_with_rule","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Close-Read: Connect to Caring for Plants "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Focus on Measurement: Read aloud the Teacher Text on the Big Chart, pausing to ask questions and talk about relative heights. "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_d-hed_prompt","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Jack traded the cow for the beans. "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Is the cow in this picture taller or shorter than Jack? How can you tell? "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Jack and his mom do not have much money for food. What could you do to help a friend who is hungry? "},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text_routine_bold","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"(MB)"}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_d-hed_prompt","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Jack climbed and climbed. "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"The beans grew into a giant "},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_emphasis_non-ital","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"beanstalk"}]},{"type":"text","text":"! How tall do you think the beanstalk is? Is it taller than a house? Taller than a mountain? "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_hilight_teacher_inst_new","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Revisit "},{"type":"element","name":"rac_highlight_teacher_inst_Italic","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"beanstalk"}]},{"type":"text","text":" Vocabulary Card. "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Jack "},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_emphasis_non-ital","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"climbed"}]},{"type":"text","text":" very high. What do you think he will find at the top? "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_hilight_teacher_inst_new","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Revisit "},{"type":"element","name":"rac_highlight_teacher_inst_Italic","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"climbed"}]},{"type":"text","text":" Vocabulary Card.  "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_d-hed_prompt","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Two giants stormed in. "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"The giants are eating dinner. How many plates are on the table? Let’s count."}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Is Jack taller or shorter than the cake? How can you tell? Do you think the giants will find him?  "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_d-hed_prompt","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Down, down, down Jack went. "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Why did Jack steal the goose?  "}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"section","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_column_heds_with_rule","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Extended Play "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Have children grow their own beanstalk! Gather clear containers, cotton balls, water, and dried lima beans. Have children hold their beans and describe what they see. Then, guide children to fill their container with cotton balls and place several beans around the edge. Add just enough water to moisten the cotton balls. Encourage children to watch as their plants grow taller over the next week. "},{"type":"element","name":"rac_child_development_icon"}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"section","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_column_heds_with_rule","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Guided Writing "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Provide a writing prompt about the steps to growing a plant, and give feedback as children draw and write in response to the prompt."}]}]}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"child-development-section","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"section-block","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_child_development_hed-green","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Child Development: Scientific Thinking "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_child_development_body","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Children at this age are already scientific thinkers. They perform their own experiments, like testing which way a ball will roll or how much water can fill a cup. Part of scientific thinking is making predictions. Each day, invite children to predict what will happen to their bean plants. Encourage them to check for changes every morning, and discuss what they see. "}]}]}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"day_5","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"week","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"section-block","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_top-left_header","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_top-left_header_all-caps","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Our earth"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_header_separator","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"|"}]},{"type":"text","text":"  WEEK 3: Caring for Plants"}]}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"circle-time-section","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"section-block","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_column_heds_no_paragraph_rule_day_5","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Connect to Language "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Ask children to describe what they remember reading, learning, and doing this week. Guide children to use the past tense, pointing out when a word does not have a regular ending: "},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"When we talk about something that already happened, we usually add -ed. We planted seeds! But the word read is different. We didn’t readed Jack and the Beanstalk–we read it. What else did we do this week? "},{"type":"element","name":"rac_child_development_icon"}]}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"section-block","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_column_heds_no_paragraph_rule_day_5","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"A Garden of Heights "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Invite children to act out a garden scene. Have children pretend to be flowers, insects, or gardeners. Ask children to show you whether they are tall or short. "}]}]}]}